From Richard Pierson Subject Re Observation re helmets In article , Norman Hamer writes Grf Dropped my Shoei RF off the seat of my bike while trying to rock it onto it's centerstand, chipped the heck out of the paint on it So I cheerfully spent on a bottle of testor's model paint and repainted the scratches and chips for minutes The question for the day is re passenger helmets, if you don't know for certain who's gonna ride with you like say you meet them at a church meeting, yeah, that's the ticket What are some guidelines Should I just pick up another shoei in my size to have a backup helmet XL , or should I maybe get an inexpensive one of a smaller size to accomodate my likely passenger My rule of thumb is Don't give rides to people that wear a bigger helmet than you , unless your taste runs that way, or they are family friends Gee, reminds me of a dancer in Hull, just over the river from Ottowa, that I saw a few years ago, for her I would a bought a bigger helmet or even her own bike or anything else she wanted There are only two types of ships in the NAVY SUBMARINES and TARGETS XS LH DoD Next raise Richard Pierson E vnet Internet , UUNET uunet bcr fist include std disclaimer My opinions are my own I Don't shop in malls, I BUY my jeans, jackets and ammo in the same store